title: [The North 'Haven Pawnery]
description: Boxes, crates, sea chests, and bulging canvas sacks are piled throughout the pawnshop in great, teetering stacks, leaving only narrow avenues between the tables of wares.  Two windows high on the plaster walls allow daylight to peek between the stacks, supplementing two small oil lanterns fixed on stout beams over the tables.
